</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Kromriff Legs.</span><hr size=1> About the &quot;how deep into CC part&quot;-  I HATE dungeons, so  I am always looking for ways to avoid going too far down into a cave.  I got my Karsin's acid my killing the top miner and the few wanderers close to the top.<br>
<br>
As far as killing Fergul- I think I actually did the final part of the quest at 56, but had another druid (54 I think) help.  Neither of us have epics.  I have helped several other people with the last step as well, so I have that fight down pretty well :)<br>
<br>
I recommend binding at the zone to EW. After you hand the harness into the broodmother- gate to the zone and run south to the giant fort.  Stand near the wall. Your pull spot is a big rock that you can stand behind.  When pulled here, you are nicely out of the way of most wanderers.  <br>
<br>
As Fergul makes his dash to the zone- run out and ensnare him. Pull him back to your nook.  Root and dot with wings and vambs.  Giants have a high fire resist- so if you are worried about mana- don't use a fire based dot like Breath of Ro.<br>
<br>
I think I have heard he has about 7k hp.  The key though is minimizing adds- which this pull spot does.<br>
<br>
Sometimes the broodmother becomes his pet.  If that is the case- then melee'rs are not a good choice, as she will help Fergul fight anything she can reach from her spot by his side.  She doesnt leave his side though- so if he is rooted, she just stands there.<br>
<br>
Good luck :)<br>
<br>
Shaiel<br>
Preserver of 59 unimplemented quests <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upadainfain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Padain Fain</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/27/01 2:44:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromriff Legs.</span><hr size=1> I soloed the quest at 54. It was very very very easy.<br>
<br>
Sceptre off of Queen at bottom of CC is easy to get with 2 people 45-50. It can be switched with a bottle of Karsin Acid, a common drop off any orc in CC. So you can kill at the top of the zone and never have a problem.<br>
<br>
Harness off of Bloodwolf is always dropped and with the number of people trashing wolves for faction (certainly on Innoruuk) one pops up on track every few minutes. <br>
<br>
Broodmother part: invis into cave, trigger with the new harness, reinvis, follow her (or run ahead) to the Giant Fort. Root/Dot the named Giant (took me about 3 minutes and was surprised how easy it was).<br>
Basically you want to avoid any form of melee with the giant as the Broodmother will be acting as his pet, although unable to leave his side. Kiting leaves you open to hits if there's any lag or if the mobs manage to warp. Fear Kiting would let you use melee's, right up til fear breaks and the melee runs smack into Broodmother's big @$$.<br>
<br>
<br>
