</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=blackwulf>Blackwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/28/01 12:37:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromriff Legs.</span><hr size=1> I did it at 54th, no epic (still), did have ES arms.  The Sceptre is easy to get, the gueen is often camped, and she always drops it.  Just find a group camping her, ask to loot, explain that it always drops and is no-drop.  Or go the acid route.<br>
<br>
Just make sure the named giants are alive when you do the quest, Fergie wasn't the last time we tried it, but we didn't think to check before turning in the harness.  Grr.<br>
<br>
Root, DoT, med, killing Fergie was no challenge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxiggin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xiggin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/30/01 5:51:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Kromriff Legs.</span><hr size=1> Why would a Druid be screwed if Broodmother becomes his pet or pull to EW zone?<br>
<br>
It only affects someone who wants to melee Fergul and I doubt druids would go that route!  <br>
<br>
Also, pulling Fergul towards the EW zone is probably one of the worst advice I have read.  Fergul and Gralk will run outside the Fort and wait for the Broodmother on the West side of the fort. You can wait to snag Fergul right by that corner. Target Fergul and as soon as he repops as the quest mob, retarget him and snare him to the safe point. Even if you miss the first snare, it is easy to run after and retarget him. Just run him between the Fort and the valley towards Thurgadin.<br>
<br>
The safe point is that little plateau between the Fort and the river.  There are no wandering mobs there and one druid could kite endlessly.   <br>
<br>
Killing Fergul will NOT be easy unless you have a very large mana pool. After all, he is still blue to a level 60.  He is very doable if you have ES Vambs or other free DOTs. However, I would not hesitate to call for help (if you solo) and have some people come to help you.  Tons of people like to kill Fergul for the faction.<br>
<br>
Finally, one has to realize that the Broodmother is highly bugged.  She might eat your harness or on the other might not despawn and pop 5-6 times the good Fergul in a row.  If you happen to see Fergul dropping the legs, do not despair. Follow the BM and if she roams for 30 minutes, the quest will recycle and a good Fergul will respawn.<br>
<br>
Good luck to you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4817.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.showMessage?topicID=4816.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.emailToFriend?topicID=4791.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.threadControl?topicID=4791.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4791.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovequests.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4791.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidicequipment">Druidic Equipment<option value="thedruidsgrovehuntingguide">Hunting Guide<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm25">PvP<option value="thedruidsgroverants">Rants<option value=